1
00:01:00,945 --> 00:01:03,305
<i>Lately, Runch and the new girl</i>

2
00:01:03,385 --> 00:01:05,385
seem awfully close.

3
00:01:06,225 --> 00:01:07,025
Maylin!

4
00:01:07,105 --> 00:01:08,945
<i>Today, you made me feel</i>

5
00:01:09,025 --> 00:01:11,465
like you have a secret life
I don't know about.

6
00:01:11,545 --> 00:01:14,225
Runch has been having problems
with her wife. They're about to break up.

7
00:01:14,305 --> 00:01:16,625
-You're so full of it.
-It's because of you

8
00:01:16,705 --> 00:01:17,985
that Runch is rebelling against me.

9
00:01:18,065 --> 00:01:21,305
I won't let anyone
hurt my wife's feelings.

10
00:01:21,385 --> 00:01:22,425
No one.

11
00:01:22,505 --> 00:01:23,465
Not even you, Mom.

12
00:01:25,985 --> 00:01:27,945
I'm sorry

13
00:01:29,465 --> 00:01:30,945
about what my mom said

14
00:01:32,105 --> 00:01:33,825
and about what happened.

15
00:01:38,025 --> 00:01:39,745
I feel really bad.

16
00:01:41,105 --> 00:01:43,185
She shouldn't have done that.

17
00:01:44,385 --> 00:01:45,745
She really shouldn't have.

18
00:02:00,105 --> 00:02:01,265
Neen.

19
00:02:04,865 --> 00:02:06,785
What's wrong?

20
00:02:08,425 --> 00:02:10,304
Are you still mad at me?

21
00:02:17,865 --> 00:02:19,185
No.

22
00:02:23,545 --> 00:02:25,585
But what happened today

23
00:02:26,745 --> 00:02:28,745
has shown me

24
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:31,945
that you'd choose to protect me.

25
00:02:39,145 --> 00:02:41,905
Still, it wasn't quick enough.

26
00:02:43,945 --> 00:02:45,305
Or good enough.

27
00:02:48,145 --> 00:02:51,385
I should've stood up for you
as soon as Mom uttered a word

28
00:02:52,625 --> 00:02:56,065
and not let her
hurt your feelings like she did.

29
00:02:59,185 --> 00:03:00,225
Runch.

30
00:03:01,945 --> 00:03:03,985
You already protected me.

31
00:03:05,705 --> 00:03:08,905
You did it in front of your mom
and everyone.

32
00:03:10,065 --> 00:03:12,065
I saw everything.

33
00:03:18,545 --> 00:03:21,625
It made me so happy I was speechless.

34
00:03:30,425 --> 00:03:31,865
Neen…

35
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:37,945
I was so afraid

36
00:03:38,585 --> 00:03:42,025
that you'd be upset.

37
00:03:46,425 --> 00:03:48,665
That you'd think

38
00:03:49,705 --> 00:03:51,785
I'd choose Mom over you.

39
00:03:55,745 --> 00:03:57,425
But today,

40
00:03:58,105 --> 00:03:59,705
I chose you.

41
00:04:00,305 --> 00:04:02,425
I chose our family.

42
00:04:05,065 --> 00:04:07,385
You are my home, Neen.

43
00:04:09,905 --> 00:04:12,065
You are my home too, Runch.

44
00:04:26,985 --> 00:04:28,145
Natee.

45
00:04:28,225 --> 00:04:30,665
I'm ready. Tell me everything.

46
00:04:30,745 --> 00:04:32,785
I don't think I want a divorce anymore.

47
00:04:34,345 --> 00:04:35,305
<i>What?</i>

48
00:04:35,945 --> 00:04:36,905
<i>What was that?</i>

49
00:04:38,025 --> 00:04:39,185
<i>Hold on.</i>

50
00:04:39,265 --> 00:04:41,905
<i>Didn't you just call me last month</i>
<i>and make a big fuss</i>

51
00:04:41,985 --> 00:04:44,025
<i>about wanting to leave her</i>
<i>because you felt hopeless?</i>

52
00:04:44,105 --> 00:04:45,425
I did.

53
00:04:45,505 --> 00:04:48,985
That was really stupid of me. But today,

54
00:04:49,065 --> 00:04:52,145
I realized it wouldn't be wise
to leave such a good woman.

55
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:54,985
<i>I love Neen so much</i>

56
00:04:55,065 --> 00:04:58,265
that I'm scared I'll make her sad again,

57
00:04:59,385 --> 00:05:03,225
or my mom will make her cry again.

58
00:05:03,785 --> 00:05:04,625
<i>Runch.</i>

59
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:08,745
Love isn't measured
by whether you've done nothing wrong,

60
00:05:09,265 --> 00:05:13,385
but by whether you'd dare to fix
this problem between her and your mom,

61
00:05:13,465 --> 00:05:16,425
and choose the one
who matters most to you.

62
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:21,465
Today, you chose Neen.
That already answers everything.

63
00:05:22,625 --> 00:05:24,265
I just realized today

64
00:05:24,825 --> 00:05:28,265
that my life is better
because I have Neen by my side.

65
00:05:30,065 --> 00:05:31,465
Thanks to her,

66
00:05:31,545 --> 00:05:35,505
I wanted to protect someone
for the first time in my life.

67
00:05:37,025 --> 00:05:38,185
I've decided.

68
00:05:38,905 --> 00:05:42,145
I won't divorce her. I won't go anywhere.

69
00:05:42,225 --> 00:05:46,185
I'll keep staying with her
until she chases me away herself.

70
00:05:47,905 --> 00:05:49,305
Good.

71
00:05:49,385 --> 00:05:51,145
<i>And if you make your wife sad again,</i>

72
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:54,425
<i>I'll fly back to Bangkok</i>
<i>just to smack you.</i>

73
00:05:56,745 --> 00:05:58,585
How cruel.

74
00:05:59,545 --> 00:06:02,385
It was the first time
she protected me, like,

75
00:06:02,465 --> 00:06:04,945
seriously protected me,
in front of her mom.

76
00:06:05,025 --> 00:06:07,945
-This situation made me realize that…
-What?

77
00:06:08,025 --> 00:06:10,465
when I said I'd divorce her…

78
00:06:10,545 --> 00:06:11,465
I was being snarky.

79
00:06:12,945 --> 00:06:14,585
You just realized that?

80
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:16,185
-We realized that long ago.
-Yeah.

81
00:06:16,265 --> 00:06:17,145
What?

82
00:06:17,225 --> 00:06:20,585
You've always been the type
to say one thing but mean another.

83
00:06:20,665 --> 00:06:23,065
I just realized that about myself.

84
00:06:23,585 --> 00:06:25,225
It's good that you won't divorce her.

85
00:06:25,305 --> 00:06:26,825
Yeah. Because if you do,

86
00:06:26,905 --> 00:06:28,705
you know who'd be the happiest?

87
00:06:28,785 --> 00:06:29,825
Who?

88
00:06:29,905 --> 00:06:30,985
Your mother-in-law.

89
00:06:33,145 --> 00:06:36,465
Look, Neen. Don't give anyone
the satisfaction of hurting you.

90
00:06:37,145 --> 00:06:39,025
Yeah. Plus,

91
00:06:39,105 --> 00:06:41,705
Runch clearly chose you.

92
00:06:43,585 --> 00:06:47,225
That means you've got
your happy ending now, right?

93
00:06:52,665 --> 00:06:54,105
Oh, Runch!

94
00:06:54,185 --> 00:06:58,185
I'm so happy you came to see me.
I was just thinking of you.

95
00:06:58,265 --> 00:07:02,225
I thought you'd be so mad at me
you'd never come see me again.

96
00:07:02,305 --> 00:07:04,345
I wasn't mad at you, Mom.

97
00:07:04,425 --> 00:07:07,665
I kind of figured.
You'd never be mad at me.

98
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:19,425
Have you recovered from that bad fall?

99
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:21,905
I'm doing better now.

100
00:07:21,985 --> 00:07:25,665
If it weren't for Maylin taking me
to the hospital yesterday,

101
00:07:25,745 --> 00:07:27,465
I'd be doing way worse.

102
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:31,225
You know, Maylin's such a sweet girl.

103
00:07:31,305 --> 00:07:33,265
She was so eager to help me.

104
00:07:33,785 --> 00:07:37,425
She looked after me and cared about me.
She's just so good to me.

105
00:07:37,505 --> 00:07:38,545
Yes, Mom.

106
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:41,665
I know she's very sweet.

107
00:07:41,745 --> 00:07:43,425
You can feel it too?

108
00:07:44,425 --> 00:07:45,585
Well, so do I.

109
00:07:45,665 --> 00:07:49,105
In that case, should we
invite her over for dinner

110
00:07:49,185 --> 00:07:52,545
to thank her for taking me
to the hospital yesterday?

111
00:07:53,265 --> 00:07:54,385
How about today?

112
00:07:54,465 --> 00:07:55,625
Mom.

113
00:07:56,345 --> 00:07:58,025
You still don't get it, do you?

114
00:07:58,105 --> 00:07:59,865
"Get it"? Get what?

115
00:08:01,545 --> 00:08:04,305
What I said yesterday.

116
00:08:04,385 --> 00:08:06,105
Don't you remember?

117
00:08:10,545 --> 00:08:12,945
<i>You have no right</i>
<i>to set me up with someone else.</i>

118
00:08:13,665 --> 00:08:16,905
You have no right to replace Neen
with someone else.

119
00:08:19,385 --> 00:08:22,265
And you have no right
to make her feel less than.

120
00:08:23,705 --> 00:08:25,465
<i>I married her.</i>

121
00:08:25,545 --> 00:08:28,265
She is my family.

122
00:08:28,345 --> 00:08:31,225
You have to respect my decision.

123
00:08:33,585 --> 00:08:35,144
What did I do wrong?

124
00:08:35,225 --> 00:08:37,465
I'm only doing this for you, Runch.

125
00:08:37,545 --> 00:08:39,985
I want you to divorce that girl.

126
00:08:40,664 --> 00:08:42,225
Don't you sigh at me.

127
00:08:42,305 --> 00:08:46,185
Your wife is so jealous
that she lashed out at everyone.

128
00:08:46,265 --> 00:08:48,945
You know the truth.
Don't you blame her for it.

129
00:08:49,025 --> 00:08:53,305
-Runch!
-Can you stop trying to destroy my family?

130
00:08:54,705 --> 00:08:56,825
So your wife slanders me,
and you believe her?

131
00:08:57,865 --> 00:09:00,105
Who would want to destroy
their own child's family?

132
00:09:00,785 --> 00:09:02,305
If you had a good wife,

133
00:09:02,385 --> 00:09:04,305
would I want you to get a divorce?

134
00:09:04,865 --> 00:09:08,825
If Neen wasn't good enough,
I'd be the one to decide.

135
00:09:08,905 --> 00:09:09,945
Mind your own business.

136
00:09:10,025 --> 00:09:11,905
What did you just say to me?

137
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:16,745
Leave me be.

138
00:09:20,825 --> 00:09:23,305
You love your wife so much
that you'd disrespect your mom

139
00:09:23,385 --> 00:09:26,705
who's always given
her all for you. How nice!

140
00:09:40,305 --> 00:09:43,345
Thank you for taking care of me
all this time.

141
00:09:44,825 --> 00:09:48,745
I never forgot that it was your support
that got me where I am today.

142
00:09:51,265 --> 00:09:53,545
From here on out,

143
00:09:53,625 --> 00:09:57,385
I'm happy to take care of you and Dad
to show you my gratitude.

144
00:10:03,825 --> 00:10:05,385
But please,

145
00:10:06,265 --> 00:10:08,545
don't destroy our family.

146
00:10:09,745 --> 00:10:11,585
Don't hurt Neen,

147
00:10:12,665 --> 00:10:15,825
either with your words or your actions.

148
00:10:15,905 --> 00:10:17,625
If I had known

149
00:10:17,705 --> 00:10:20,305
that you'd be like this
after marrying her,

150
00:10:20,385 --> 00:10:22,025
I would've done everything to stop you!

151
00:10:22,105 --> 00:10:23,345
I love Neen.

152
00:10:23,425 --> 00:10:26,185
-We love each other.
-But I hate her!

153
00:10:36,145 --> 00:10:37,585
We've talked.

154
00:10:38,385 --> 00:10:39,825
We've had a proper conversation.

155
00:10:41,505 --> 00:10:43,345
We've compromised.

156
00:10:46,825 --> 00:10:49,545
-So if you keep this up--
-What will you do?

157
00:10:50,265 --> 00:10:51,825
Will you leave your own mom

158
00:10:51,905 --> 00:10:53,785
to be with your wife?

159
00:10:54,905 --> 00:10:58,865
Just wait and see
how long she'll really stick with you.

160
00:11:02,705 --> 00:11:05,665
I'm telling you one last time.

161
00:11:07,105 --> 00:11:11,105
You'd better stop whatever it is
you're about to think or do.

162
00:11:13,105 --> 00:11:16,945
Stop putting someone
in between our relationship.

163
00:11:18,425 --> 00:11:21,585
Stay out of my family's business.

164
00:11:24,705 --> 00:11:26,465
You're pretty cocky for someone so stupid.

165
00:11:27,145 --> 00:11:28,745
Keep letting that family

166
00:11:28,825 --> 00:11:31,185
keep you down
for the rest of your life, then.

167
00:11:52,905 --> 00:11:53,945
Runch.

168
00:11:54,865 --> 00:11:55,985
Dad.

169
00:11:57,545 --> 00:11:58,905
Done talking to your mom?

170
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:00,105
Yes.

171
00:12:01,305 --> 00:12:03,345
I don't know
if that's the end of it, though.

172
00:12:04,585 --> 00:12:06,705
She'll never change.

173
00:12:07,345 --> 00:12:09,625
Don't expect her to change.

174
00:12:09,705 --> 00:12:11,225
She's a lost cause.

175
00:12:17,705 --> 00:12:19,905
I know what to do.

176
00:12:22,505 --> 00:12:24,265
I just don't want to do it.

177
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:30,385
If you want to live your own life,

178
00:12:30,465 --> 00:12:32,345
there's only one way.

179
00:12:37,705 --> 00:12:40,785
Mom used to be my childhood hero.

180
00:12:42,065 --> 00:12:44,705
She used to be
someone I loved and respected.

181
00:12:48,345 --> 00:12:49,785
But today,

182
00:12:50,505 --> 00:12:54,745
that's no longer my impression of her.

183
00:12:56,945 --> 00:12:58,905
Neen really loves you.

184
00:12:59,585 --> 00:13:02,545
She's the life partner that you chose.

185
00:13:03,505 --> 00:13:08,105
No matter what you do, speak, or decide,

186
00:13:08,905 --> 00:13:11,305
remember to really think of her.

187
00:13:13,105 --> 00:13:14,465
As for your mom,

188
00:13:15,145 --> 00:13:16,545
you just talked to her.

189
00:13:16,625 --> 00:13:20,705
I take it you can decide
what to do now, right?

190
00:13:22,065 --> 00:13:24,985
It's time you made
a firm decision for your wife.

191
00:13:29,025 --> 00:13:30,465
Yes, Dad.

192
00:13:48,385 --> 00:13:51,785
Our daughter became so different
because of that girl.

193
00:13:53,825 --> 00:13:57,385
She's all grown now, honey.
She has her own family.

194
00:13:57,465 --> 00:13:59,825
Family? What family?

195
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:05,945
She's my daughter. I raised her myself.

196
00:14:06,905 --> 00:14:09,545
But today, she talked back to me.

197
00:14:10,225 --> 00:14:12,985
She defended that girl in front of me.

198
00:14:18,345 --> 00:14:22,065
Do you know how hurt I was?

199
00:14:27,105 --> 00:14:28,345
You know,

200
00:14:29,825 --> 00:14:31,465
you never asked our daughter

201
00:14:31,545 --> 00:14:35,185
how uncomfortable your actions made her.

202
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:40,345
You're siding with that girl?

203
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:43,585
I'm siding with what's right.

204
00:14:44,745 --> 00:14:46,545
You've got to stop.

205
00:14:47,305 --> 00:14:49,905
Not everything will go your way.

206
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:58,505
So you don't understand me either, do you?

207
00:15:00,345 --> 00:15:01,705
I do understand you.

208
00:15:02,545 --> 00:15:04,105
But I don't agree with you.

209
00:15:04,185 --> 00:15:08,505
And I won't let you hurt our daughter
just because you don't want to lose her.

210
00:15:15,065 --> 00:15:16,825
It's okay. Come here.

211
00:15:18,825 --> 00:15:20,505
It's okay.

212
00:15:55,865 --> 00:16:01,985
RUNCH'S HOME

213
00:16:23,225 --> 00:16:26,865
HAPPY MOTHER'S DAY

214
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:49,265
Good job, honey.

215
00:16:57,745 --> 00:16:59,625
Are you hungry?

216
00:17:02,225 --> 00:17:03,345
Want some?

217
00:17:05,745 --> 00:17:06,905
Okay.

218
00:17:09,305 --> 00:17:11,265
Watch. Do it like so.

219
00:17:16,145 --> 00:17:17,345
-Thanks.
-Okay!

220
00:17:18,025 --> 00:17:19,704
There's our last one.

221
00:17:19,785 --> 00:17:20,745
Our last one.

222
00:17:25,265 --> 00:17:26,585
Your change is five baht.

223
00:17:26,665 --> 00:17:28,305
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

224
00:17:29,425 --> 00:17:31,785
-Hey, honey. Are you tired?
-Hi.

225
00:17:31,865 --> 00:17:34,385
I missed you. Let me carry your bag.

226
00:17:34,465 --> 00:17:35,705
-Thank you.
-Okay.

227
00:17:36,265 --> 00:17:37,945
Help me sell these, will you?

228
00:17:38,025 --> 00:17:40,785
-Help you?
-There. That one, honey.

229
00:17:43,745 --> 00:17:45,425
Your change is five baht.

230
00:17:46,265 --> 00:17:47,785
Got a lot of homework today?

231
00:17:47,865 --> 00:17:50,305
-There's kind of a lot.
-I missed you.

232
00:17:51,345 --> 00:17:53,025
<i>I won't leave you.</i>

233
00:17:53,105 --> 00:17:56,425
<i>I'll always love you</i>
<i>more than anyone. I promise.</i>

234
00:18:00,145 --> 00:18:02,025
Then today,

235
00:18:04,705 --> 00:18:07,145
why are you choosing someone else over me?

236
00:18:14,545 --> 00:18:15,665
Runch…

237
00:18:38,665 --> 00:18:39,985
Runch.

238
00:18:40,065 --> 00:18:43,105
May I speak to you for a moment?

239
00:18:44,145 --> 00:18:46,705
Of course. Please, have a seat.

240
00:18:52,105 --> 00:18:54,225
About everything that happened,

241
00:18:54,825 --> 00:18:56,985
at first I didn't know

242
00:18:57,065 --> 00:19:00,465
that Aunt Ging was trying
to set me up with you.

243
00:19:02,185 --> 00:19:05,145
I swear I had no idea,

244
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:08,425
and I feel very bad

245
00:19:09,065 --> 00:19:11,825
about inconveniencing you.

246
00:19:13,465 --> 00:19:15,465
And Ms. Peeracha too.

247
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:20,185
Thank you for letting me know.

248
00:19:24,105 --> 00:19:25,865
I want to apologize, Runch.

249
00:19:26,865 --> 00:19:30,105
If me working closely with you
and my ignorance

250
00:19:30,825 --> 00:19:33,465
caused you
to have problems with your wife,

251
00:19:34,185 --> 00:19:36,265
I'd rather

252
00:19:37,025 --> 00:19:40,225
we stay just coworkers.

253
00:19:41,945 --> 00:19:44,585
Thank you for understanding

254
00:19:45,185 --> 00:19:47,705
and having the courage to speak up.

255
00:19:49,585 --> 00:19:53,425
I don't want anyone
to be in this kind of situation.

256
00:19:53,505 --> 00:19:57,665
Especially not you, Maylin.
It's really unfair.

257
00:20:00,585 --> 00:20:02,185
I understand.

258
00:20:03,385 --> 00:20:05,865
I respect your relationship.

259
00:20:05,945 --> 00:20:08,745
Ever since the day
I found out you were married,

260
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:12,785
I've never dared cross the line.

261
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:19,105
Then let's work hard together
since you're on my team.

262
00:20:28,745 --> 00:20:30,745
Thank you, Runch.

263
00:20:33,185 --> 00:20:36,305
Thank you for allowing me
to speak with you.

264
00:20:37,065 --> 00:20:40,905
I didn't want to make excuses or anything.

265
00:20:40,985 --> 00:20:43,545
I just wanted to make things clear.

266
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:48,225
I think of Runch as a friend.

267
00:20:49,305 --> 00:20:50,785
Nothing more.

268
00:20:50,865 --> 00:20:55,105
I have no intention of stealing anyone
or getting in between any couple.

269
00:20:56,665 --> 00:20:58,825
I respect every relationship.

270
00:20:59,345 --> 00:21:04,265
Plus, I'm well aware that no one
should meddle in anyone's marriage.

271
00:21:05,025 --> 00:21:07,185
Not even if they mean well.

272
00:21:07,825 --> 00:21:09,545
I came here today

273
00:21:10,985 --> 00:21:12,945
not so you would believe me.

274
00:21:13,665 --> 00:21:15,665
But it's so you could rest easy

275
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:21,345
that at least I won't be the one
to put your relationship

276
00:21:21,945 --> 00:21:23,265
in jeopardy.

277
00:21:25,225 --> 00:21:27,505
I hope you understand.

278
00:21:35,545 --> 00:21:36,745
Yes.

279
00:21:38,065 --> 00:21:40,265
Thank you for letting me know.

280
00:21:42,105 --> 00:21:44,625
It shows that you're sincere.

281
00:21:52,465 --> 00:21:54,225
-Hello.
-Hello, honey.

282
00:21:54,305 --> 00:21:55,985
Sorry for being late, Auntie.

283
00:21:56,065 --> 00:21:58,105
I was stuck in traffic.

284
00:21:58,185 --> 00:22:01,905
It's okay. I just got here too.
Have a seat.

285
00:22:10,625 --> 00:22:13,785
I'm really sorry about the other day.

286
00:22:13,865 --> 00:22:18,585
I didn't think it'd turn into such a mess.
I don't want you to feel bad.

287
00:22:21,785 --> 00:22:23,705
No worries, Auntie.

288
00:22:23,785 --> 00:22:27,585
I understand. It was an awkward situation.

289
00:22:29,305 --> 00:22:32,185
Maylin, can I be honest with you?

290
00:22:32,265 --> 00:22:34,145
I really adore you.

291
00:22:34,225 --> 00:22:37,985
And I want you to marry my daughter
more than anyone.

292
00:22:41,625 --> 00:22:44,505
-Can I be honest with you too?
-Of course.

293
00:22:44,585 --> 00:22:46,705
I like people who are straightforward.

294
00:22:50,145 --> 00:22:52,585
I don't want to be anyone's tool.

295
00:22:56,865 --> 00:23:00,105
And I don't want to
steal anyone's wife, either.

296
00:23:01,665 --> 00:23:03,345
I respect Runch's marriage

297
00:23:03,425 --> 00:23:06,185
and Runch's decisions.

298
00:23:07,505 --> 00:23:10,625
With everything that happened,
I want to end it here.

299
00:23:14,785 --> 00:23:17,425
Thank you for inviting me
for dinner, Auntie.

300
00:23:18,625 --> 00:23:21,265
But I have to go meet someone,
so if you'll excuse me.

301
00:23:22,585 --> 00:23:23,745
See you later.

302
00:23:55,825 --> 00:23:58,705
<i>I don't want to be anyone's tool.</i>

303
00:23:58,785 --> 00:24:02,185
And I don't want to
steal anyone's wife, either.

304
00:24:02,905 --> 00:24:05,185
I respect Runch's marriage

305
00:24:05,265 --> 00:24:07,585
and Runch's decisions.

306
00:24:08,665 --> 00:24:12,225
With everything that happened,
I want to end it here.

307
00:24:16,425 --> 00:24:20,545
-I love Neen. We love each other.
-But I hate her!

308
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,945
We've talked.
We've had a proper conversation.

309
00:24:23,025 --> 00:24:24,785
We've compromised.

310
00:24:24,865 --> 00:24:27,745
-So if you keep this up--
-What will you do?

311
00:24:27,825 --> 00:24:29,465
Will you leave your own mom

312
00:24:29,545 --> 00:24:31,545
to be with your wife?

313
00:24:31,625 --> 00:24:34,665
I'm telling you one last time.

314
00:24:34,745 --> 00:24:37,625
You'd better stop whatever it is
you're about to think

315
00:24:37,705 --> 00:24:39,025
or do.

316
00:24:39,105 --> 00:24:42,945
Stop putting someone
in between our relationship.

317
00:24:44,425 --> 00:24:47,625
Stay out of my family's business.

318
00:25:40,665 --> 00:25:43,185
I gave her one last warning

319
00:25:43,265 --> 00:25:45,865
to stop messing with our family.

320
00:25:46,825 --> 00:25:49,345
And if she still does,

321
00:25:50,025 --> 00:25:52,905
I'll get out of her life myself.

322
00:25:54,105 --> 00:25:55,305
Runch!

323
00:25:57,225 --> 00:25:59,225
Neen, do you remember?

324
00:26:01,185 --> 00:26:04,065
A long time ago, you asked me

325
00:26:05,625 --> 00:26:09,145
who I'd choose, between you

326
00:26:09,225 --> 00:26:10,705
and my mom.

327
00:26:15,505 --> 00:26:17,665
Will you stay by my side?

328
00:26:19,825 --> 00:26:21,705
So we're not getting
divorced anymore, right?

329
00:26:23,185 --> 00:26:25,785
No, we're not.

330
00:26:27,105 --> 00:26:29,385
We've been through a lot.

331
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:33,145
We've given each other a chance.

332
00:26:33,225 --> 00:26:36,305
We've expected things and been let down

333
00:26:36,385 --> 00:26:37,985
over and over.

334
00:26:39,585 --> 00:26:41,825
I hope this was the last time.

335
00:26:43,625 --> 00:26:46,185
I really want us to be happy together.

336
00:26:46,265 --> 00:26:49,225
I want us to be happy together too.

337
00:27:08,145 --> 00:27:10,945
How are you so pretty
even when you're asleep?

338
00:27:12,505 --> 00:27:14,305
I heard that.

339
00:27:17,825 --> 00:27:19,705
Well, do you like what you heard?

340
00:27:20,985 --> 00:27:22,225
Of course.

341
00:27:22,905 --> 00:27:24,585
I like it when you compliment me.

342
00:27:25,465 --> 00:27:27,225
You're the prettiest.

343
00:27:29,025 --> 00:27:30,385
How sweet.

344
00:27:31,425 --> 00:27:35,145
Since I'm being sweet,
do you have a reward for me?

345
00:27:39,945 --> 00:27:41,065
Satisfied?

346
00:27:44,225 --> 00:27:45,865
No.

347
00:27:52,505 --> 00:27:53,905
What are you doing, Runch?

348
00:27:53,985 --> 00:27:56,265
It's morning time, you know.

349
00:27:58,025 --> 00:27:59,785
Why?

350
00:27:59,865 --> 00:28:03,265
Who says we can't do this in the morning?

351
00:28:56,185 --> 00:28:57,985
Yes, Dad?

352
00:28:59,345 --> 00:29:01,985
What? Mom ran away from home?

353
00:29:05,865 --> 00:29:08,745
-She won't pick up?
-Yeah.

354
00:29:08,825 --> 00:29:11,825
I'll go see if she's
at her best friend's house.

355
00:29:12,345 --> 00:29:13,705
I'll come with you.

356
00:29:27,945 --> 00:29:29,065
Mom!

357
00:29:34,985 --> 00:29:36,625
Runch.

358
00:29:40,745 --> 00:29:42,985
I don't want to go home.

359
00:29:44,825 --> 00:29:46,745
What happened, Mom?

360
00:29:55,025 --> 00:29:57,985
Last night, I spent all night thinking

361
00:29:58,065 --> 00:30:01,385
that maybe I really am
the troublemaker of this family.

362
00:30:02,785 --> 00:30:04,545
Please don't say that, honey.

363
00:30:04,625 --> 00:30:06,865
Don't start it that way.
I don't want to fight.

364
00:30:07,865 --> 00:30:10,945
You don't want to fight,
yet you said it as if I was selfish.

365
00:30:11,025 --> 00:30:13,625
As if I should get out
of my daughter's life.

366
00:30:13,705 --> 00:30:16,065
-That's not what I said.
-But it's what you think.

367
00:30:16,145 --> 00:30:19,145
You sided with her.
You sided with that girl.

368
00:30:20,505 --> 00:30:23,105
What about me? Who am I in this family?

369
00:30:23,185 --> 00:30:25,505
You're my wife
and the mother of our child.

370
00:30:25,585 --> 00:30:27,905
But you don't own anyone's life.

371
00:30:27,985 --> 00:30:29,905
So I don't matter, then?

372
00:30:29,985 --> 00:30:31,825
I'm just taking up space in this house.

373
00:30:33,065 --> 00:30:35,105
You're taking it too far.

374
00:30:36,545 --> 00:30:38,145
Or do you want me to leave?

375
00:30:39,705 --> 00:30:42,425
Say it. Say it loud and clear.

376
00:30:42,505 --> 00:30:44,705
"Leave the house."

377
00:30:44,785 --> 00:30:47,665
You're trying
to start a fight, aren't you?

378
00:30:51,185 --> 00:30:54,225
I'm just wondering

379
00:30:54,305 --> 00:30:57,905
if there's still a place for me
in this house.

380
00:30:57,985 --> 00:31:00,265
If you want to stay, stop hurting others.

381
00:31:00,345 --> 00:31:03,625
But if you can't stop, then leave
and compose yourself for a bit.

382
00:31:04,905 --> 00:31:06,025
Good.

383
00:31:06,785 --> 00:31:08,225
You finally said it.

384
00:31:09,345 --> 00:31:11,185
I'm not kicking you out, Ging.

385
00:31:11,265 --> 00:31:13,825
I don't need your excuses. I don't.

386
00:31:14,625 --> 00:31:17,785
I heard you loud and clear. Pong!

387
00:31:18,545 --> 00:31:19,745
Pong!

388
00:31:21,425 --> 00:31:24,105
Pong, why'd you kick me out?

389
00:31:24,185 --> 00:31:25,745
What?

390
00:31:25,825 --> 00:31:28,105
Your dad kicked me out.

391
00:31:28,745 --> 00:31:30,905
He said I'm a troublemaker.

392
00:31:31,665 --> 00:31:34,105
All I do is cause trouble for others.

393
00:31:37,465 --> 00:31:40,265
‎Mom, maybe you got him wrong.

394
00:31:40,825 --> 00:31:44,745
He wouldn't say something like that.
He's not a heartless man.

395
00:31:45,385 --> 00:31:47,665
You always side with your dad.

396
00:31:48,265 --> 00:31:50,465
How come you never believe what I say?

397
00:31:51,025 --> 00:31:54,545
I'm the one who's hurt,
the one who got kicked out.

398
00:31:54,625 --> 00:31:57,105
Yet no one's siding with me.

399
00:32:02,225 --> 00:32:05,505
Well, so far, we can't trust
anything you said.

400
00:32:12,945 --> 00:32:15,585
I've got no one left.

401
00:32:16,665 --> 00:32:20,065
I can't even go home
because my husband doesn't want me.

402
00:32:20,145 --> 00:32:22,345
I don't know where to go anymore.

403
00:32:35,505 --> 00:32:37,825
Can I stay here a while?

404
00:32:40,065 --> 00:32:42,425
At least just temporarily.

405
00:32:42,505 --> 00:32:46,065
I just need a roof over my head.

406
00:32:47,785 --> 00:32:49,105
No.

407
00:32:54,265 --> 00:32:56,385
You have your own place.

408
00:32:56,465 --> 00:32:59,385
If you have a problem with Dad,
you should go home and talk it out.

409
00:32:59,465 --> 00:33:02,625
You can't fix the problem
by moving to someone else's house.

410
00:33:07,865 --> 00:33:10,785
I'll call Dad and tell him
to pick you up now.

411
00:33:10,865 --> 00:33:13,705
Married couples should talk
when there's a problem.

412
00:33:13,785 --> 00:33:15,905
You shouldn't be coming to other couples.

413
00:33:18,505 --> 00:33:21,865
-Runch, Runch!
-Please calm down.

414
00:33:22,785 --> 00:33:25,305
Neen, please calm down.

415
00:33:25,385 --> 00:33:26,585
I am.

416
00:33:26,665 --> 00:33:29,305
And I'm being reasonable, not emotional.

417
00:33:37,945 --> 00:33:40,785
Ging, please come home with me.

418
00:33:40,865 --> 00:33:43,745
I shouldn't have said it.
I didn't mean to kick you out.

419
00:33:43,825 --> 00:33:45,025
Don't apologize.

420
00:33:45,865 --> 00:33:47,985
Everything you said is true.

421
00:33:48,065 --> 00:33:49,825
You don't want me anymore.

422
00:33:49,905 --> 00:33:52,425
-It's not that. It's just that--
-Enough.

423
00:33:53,625 --> 00:33:57,065
Like I said, I'm not going back
to that house.

424
00:34:01,305 --> 00:34:02,185
Mom.

425
00:34:03,785 --> 00:34:05,025
You have to go home.

426
00:34:05,105 --> 00:34:06,705
I'll give you a ride.

427
00:34:06,785 --> 00:34:10,264
Dad's already here,
so this should settle it.

428
00:34:13,225 --> 00:34:14,545
Let's go.

429
00:34:16,025 --> 00:34:16,865
Neen!

430
00:34:16,945 --> 00:34:18,425
-Mom!
-Ging!

431
00:34:18,505 --> 00:34:20,185
-What are you doing?
-Mom.

432
00:34:21,945 --> 00:34:23,025
Neen.

433
00:34:23,105 --> 00:34:24,225
Neen.

434
00:34:24,945 --> 00:34:26,744
I'm sorry, honey.

435
00:34:28,105 --> 00:34:29,225
It was my fault.

436
00:34:29,304 --> 00:34:31,344
I treated you so badly.

437
00:34:31,425 --> 00:34:35,744
I tried to set Runch up with another woman
without caring about your feelings.

438
00:34:36,784 --> 00:34:39,905
I was selfish.
I only thought about myself.

439
00:34:39,985 --> 00:34:42,545
I was so scared I'd lose my daughter
that I forgot

440
00:34:42,625 --> 00:34:44,665
you're her wife.

441
00:34:46,665 --> 00:34:49,505
Please. I beg of you.

442
00:34:49,585 --> 00:34:51,185
Let me stay here.

443
00:34:51,985 --> 00:34:54,145
I won't be a burden.

444
00:34:54,225 --> 00:34:56,145
Please? I don't want to go home yet.

445
00:34:56,225 --> 00:34:58,665
-Please, Neen. I don't want to go home.
-Mom.

446
00:34:58,745 --> 00:35:00,625
-Please get up.
-Honey.

447
00:35:00,705 --> 00:35:02,105
-Runch!
-Please don't do this.

448
00:35:02,185 --> 00:35:03,785
-Please get up.
-Come on.

449
00:35:03,865 --> 00:35:05,825
-Please get up, Mom.
-I don't want to go home.

450
00:35:14,905 --> 00:35:16,625
Neen,

451
00:35:16,705 --> 00:35:18,505
if you're still mad at me,

452
00:35:19,225 --> 00:35:20,825
I don't see any reason to get up.

453
00:35:20,905 --> 00:35:22,345
-Mom.
-Mom!

454
00:35:22,425 --> 00:35:25,465
This isn't right, Mom. Please get up.

455
00:35:25,545 --> 00:35:27,985
-Neen. Neen.
-Mom!

456
00:35:28,065 --> 00:35:29,705
Please listen to me.

457
00:35:29,785 --> 00:35:32,265
I really am sorry.

458
00:35:32,345 --> 00:35:33,905
I'll treat you better.

459
00:35:33,985 --> 00:35:35,585
I'll stay out of your business.

460
00:35:35,665 --> 00:35:38,265
-I won't hurt you anymore. I just need…
-No…

461
00:35:38,345 --> 00:35:39,465
…a roof over my head!

462
00:35:39,545 --> 00:35:41,865
-Please, Neen!
-Mom, Mom!

463
00:35:41,945 --> 00:35:43,545
Please, Neen.

464
00:35:47,305 --> 00:35:49,785
-Mom.
-Neen.

465
00:35:49,865 --> 00:35:51,305
-Please get up.
-Get up.

466
00:35:53,945 --> 00:35:56,145
-Honey. What? Honey!
-Mom!

467
00:35:56,225 --> 00:35:57,225
-Ging!
-Mom!

468
00:35:57,305 --> 00:35:58,545
-Honey!
-Mom!

469
00:35:58,625 --> 00:36:00,025
Honey!

470
00:36:00,105 --> 00:36:01,625
Honey!

471
00:36:01,705 --> 00:36:03,225
Neen.

472
00:36:04,545 --> 00:36:06,745
We'll have to let her stay for a bit.

473
00:36:10,585 --> 00:36:13,905
Apparently, yeah.

474
00:36:16,665 --> 00:36:18,225
I'm sorry.

475
00:36:22,385 --> 00:36:23,825
Why are you sorry?

476
00:36:24,625 --> 00:36:26,265
You didn't do anything wrong.

477
00:36:30,945 --> 00:36:31,905
Look,

478
00:36:32,625 --> 00:36:36,345
I only gave up because I saw
that she really felt guilty.

479
00:36:39,065 --> 00:36:40,385
But all I ask

480
00:36:40,465 --> 00:36:44,105
is that she was being genuine.

481
00:36:44,745 --> 00:36:46,545
Because otherwise,

482
00:36:47,185 --> 00:36:50,185
I'll have to ask you
to take her home, Dad.

483
00:36:50,265 --> 00:36:52,505
Yeah, I understand.

484
00:36:52,585 --> 00:36:55,425
Sorry if I made you two uncomfortable

485
00:36:55,505 --> 00:36:58,665
because of the issue between me and her.

486
00:37:00,305 --> 00:37:04,225
Thank you, Dad. I really don't want
anyone to feel uncomfortable.

487
00:37:05,145 --> 00:37:09,385
I just want our privacy to be respected,
no matter what.

488
00:37:18,785 --> 00:37:20,225
<i>Yad, please open the door.</i>

489
00:37:25,345 --> 00:37:27,665
<i>You won't open it? Then I will.</i>

490
00:37:40,905 --> 00:37:42,105
I don't think

491
00:37:42,785 --> 00:37:44,225
that was a ghost.

492
00:37:44,745 --> 00:37:46,785
It sounded like a real knock on our door.

493
00:37:52,545 --> 00:37:53,985
Runch. Runch.

494
00:38:05,505 --> 00:38:08,705
-It's a ghost!
-It's a ghost!

495
00:38:08,785 --> 00:38:10,825
Why are you yelling?

496
00:38:10,905 --> 00:38:13,585
Hey, it's just me.
What do you mean, "a ghost"?

497
00:38:15,745 --> 00:38:18,585
See? It's just me.

498
00:38:18,665 --> 00:38:22,025
Mom, you scared us.

499
00:38:24,905 --> 00:38:26,265
Is something wrong, Mom?

500
00:38:28,145 --> 00:38:31,505
I couldn't sleep.
I'm not used to this place.

501
00:38:31,585 --> 00:38:34,185
There isn't a TV in my room, either.

502
00:38:34,265 --> 00:38:37,705
I'm scared. Can you sleep with me, Runch?

503
00:38:52,225 --> 00:38:53,745
She's asleep already?

504
00:39:03,385 --> 00:39:06,585
-This brat!
-Got a problem?

505
00:39:06,665 --> 00:39:08,265
Shut up!

506
00:39:16,145 --> 00:39:17,545
She's sleep-talking?

507
00:39:21,905 --> 00:39:23,385
You underestimated me.

508
00:39:24,185 --> 00:39:25,145
I'm not one…

509
00:39:26,385 --> 00:39:28,385
to get fooled so easily.

510
00:39:28,465 --> 00:39:31,985
You think you're tough? What a loser.

511
00:39:36,825 --> 00:39:39,945
You think you can fool me
by pretending to be nice?

512
00:39:46,385 --> 00:39:49,425
I'm talking to you.
Why are you quiet? How shameless.

513
00:39:50,425 --> 00:39:54,985
You're so shameless
that you deserve an award for it.

514
00:40:30,785 --> 00:40:34,665
Finally, that old loudmouth's
moved in with me.

515
00:40:35,945 --> 00:40:38,225
Wait. She really did?

516
00:40:39,345 --> 00:40:41,865
What? Neen, how come you're giving in?

517
00:40:41,945 --> 00:40:44,785
-This is so unlike you.
-I'm not giving in.

518
00:40:46,345 --> 00:40:48,305
I'm just monitoring her.

519
00:40:49,945 --> 00:40:51,985
She obviously faked it.

520
00:40:53,265 --> 00:40:56,585
She was way too nice.
She apologized too easily.

521
00:40:56,665 --> 00:40:59,225
It's like she took ten acting classes.

522
00:40:59,305 --> 00:41:00,545
Well,

523
00:41:00,625 --> 00:41:02,305
does Runch believe her mom?

524
00:41:02,385 --> 00:41:04,105
She does wholeheartedly.

525
00:41:04,185 --> 00:41:05,505
I knew it. Told you.

526
00:41:05,585 --> 00:41:07,705
She believes her mom feels guilty.

527
00:41:07,785 --> 00:41:09,425
And that's just how she is.

528
00:41:09,505 --> 00:41:12,865
When she believes something,
she believes it so, so strongly.

529
00:41:12,945 --> 00:41:17,025
Then what do you do now
since you're the only one who sees it?

530
00:41:17,105 --> 00:41:18,345
Yeah.

531
00:41:19,425 --> 00:41:23,545
I'll have to show Runch
her mom's true colors.

532
00:41:26,105 --> 00:41:27,425
Oops.

533
00:41:27,505 --> 00:41:30,025
This isn't just family drama anymore.

534
00:41:30,105 --> 00:41:32,225
This is a war between a wife
and her mother-in-law.

535
00:41:32,985 --> 00:41:33,825
Yeah.

536
00:41:34,465 --> 00:41:36,905
And I must win this war.

537
00:41:57,985 --> 00:42:02,785
Hello, Runch? I'm at the beach,
but I don't see you.

538
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:12,065
I see it.

539
00:42:31,785 --> 00:42:35,545
<i>Neen, follow the trail of seashells.</i>

540
00:43:15,625 --> 00:43:19,985
<i>Follow the trail of rocks.</i>
<i>Don't be afraid. Just keep walking, Neen.</i>

541
00:43:41,665 --> 00:43:43,265
What are you trying to do, Runch?

542
00:43:51,105 --> 00:43:52,425
You know…

543
00:43:54,065 --> 00:43:57,345
Ever since the day I decided
to love a woman,

544
00:43:58,505 --> 00:44:01,185
I've known my life wouldn't be easy.

545
00:44:04,345 --> 00:44:06,585
And if it weren't for you,

546
00:44:07,825 --> 00:44:10,305
I wouldn't want to keep moving on.

547
00:44:44,985 --> 00:44:47,825
I may not be a perfect woman…

548
00:44:49,225 --> 00:44:50,825
I have responsibilities.

549
00:44:52,905 --> 00:44:54,785
I have my own world

550
00:44:55,705 --> 00:44:56,945
that can feel heavy at times.

551
00:44:58,665 --> 00:45:00,585
But if you accept,

552
00:45:02,225 --> 00:45:06,705
I want you to be there by my side,
in my world, on every good day

553
00:45:06,785 --> 00:45:08,945
and every difficult day.

554
00:45:11,625 --> 00:45:13,385
Will you marry me?

555
00:45:15,185 --> 00:45:17,265
Will you be my wife

556
00:45:18,465 --> 00:45:19,945
and my family?

557
00:45:26,185 --> 00:45:27,465
Runch.

558
00:45:28,185 --> 00:45:29,665
Well…

559
00:45:31,505 --> 00:45:33,225
I…

560
00:45:41,065 --> 00:45:42,145
Yes, I will.

561
00:46:27,265 --> 00:46:29,505
We agreed to stay married.

562
00:46:31,745 --> 00:46:35,105
I'll make sure
you get out of Runch's life.

563
00:46:36,945 --> 00:46:39,705
A tamarind tree
to ward off evil spirits.

564
00:46:39,785 --> 00:46:42,705
Get all those trees out of here.
I don't like them.

565
00:46:42,785 --> 00:46:44,585
Please listen to me, Neen!

566
00:46:44,665 --> 00:46:47,385
Stop bullshitting me! Stop it!

567
00:46:47,465 --> 00:46:48,945
Neen, that's enough!

568
00:47:33,145 --> 00:47:35,505
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

